Naledi Shange, News24Car accident. (KZN EMS) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Durban- &nbsp;A 25-year-old man was killed when a bus and bakkie collided on the M1 highway near Richmond on Saturday morning, said KwaZulu-Natal EMS.&nbsp;"Fifteen other people have sustained injuries and were treated by paramedics from the KZN Department of Health&rsquo;s Emergency Medical Services and several private ambulance services," said spokesperson Robert Mckenzie.&nbsp;Four were in a critical condition while the other 11 had sustained serious injuries.The group was treated on scene before being transported to various hospitals.&nbsp;The cause of the crash was not immediately clear.&nbsp;24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.